                      "notes":  "Bith Gadgeteer Engineer built for a level 5 Clone Wars Republic mission. Species traits: speed 30, Detail Oriented, Keen Hearing and Smell, Musician, Programmer. Languages: Galactic Basic, Bith, binary/droid-oriented mission language by GM approval. Saving throws: Constitution and Intelligence. Skills: Investigation, Technology, Piloting, Lore, Medicine. Technology is marked expertise for app simplicity; if your GM wants Bith Programmer to apply only to computer-related Technology checks, set technology.expertise to false and use the Computer Slicing custom roll instead. Engineer 5 core values: 12 tech powers known, 10 base tech points, max power level 3rd, Potent Aptitude d6, 5 modification slots. Nim is using 4 harness modifications, one over proficiency bonus, so tech point max is entered as 9. Harness modifications assumed: Integrated Inhibitor, Sentry Turret, Oil Spill, Shocking Barrier. Tech powers known: Ion Blast, Mending, On/Off, Analyze, Energy Shield, Kolto Pack, Smoke Cloud, Tactical Barrier, Repair Droid, Hold Droid, Lock, Invisibility to Cameras, Scramble Interface. Combat gear: combat suit infused to +1 AC, light pistol, vibrodagger, wristpad, tinker\u0027s implements, gadgeteer\u0027s implements. Personality: precise, over-formal, nasal technical specialist who protects allies with barriers, complains politely about unsafe equipment, and treats droid warfare as an engineering hygiene problem."
